open the repository of a github user to access what is in there
choose the file in which you want to make any changes lying in the repository
after that once you have searched the file you want to change open it
fork the repository 
click on the edit pencil icon which is at the right side of the middle window
edit the file 
press on the commit changes tab button which should be at the bottom of the editable window
changes will be saved
go to the previous directory from the top of the editable window
click on the creat pull request button and edit your description to your work or changes you made
Congratullations. . ! you have made your pull request...!
note:
its an easy way to edit directly online but upon entering wrong code professionally site should get down instantly and immediately..
